In vi-mode the 'u' key is bounded to 
> vi-undo-change

According "man zshzle"


> vi-undo-change (unbound) (u) (unbound)
> Undo the last text modification.  If repeated, redo the modification.

Just try out :

> bindkey -M vicmd 'u' undo

best regards
Ray




